      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BRAVE WASP (4) won well fresh and has been treading water since, beaten 3.9L at Belmont last time out. This is slightly easier this time around, but back to 1000m may hold the key. Can lob in a midfield position and get over the top to return to winning ways. PAINT IT RED (2) pulled up with an issue last start and has spent some time away dealing with that. Her best is good enough though and the inside draw is a big tick. The claim of Webster comes in handy and a forward showing is on the cards. SNIPER'S SON (1) won over this track and trip two back before tackling a stronger race on Saturday where he finished midfield. Back to the scene of the crime is a bonus and he should be up front from the outset. Can give them something to chase. SOMETHING ROYAL (7) won't be far away if he runs up to recent efforts. HANG GLIDER (5) won't be far away coming back to his preferred trip.",
